se lawyers, defendants, and translators-about their experiences and practices to explain how this system functions, and how its functioning has affected the conflict. Her lucid, richly detailed, and theoretically sophisticated study highlights the array of problems and debates that characterize Israel's military courts as it asks how the law is deployed to protect and further the interests of the Israeli state and how it has been used to articulate and defend the rights of Palestinians living under occupation.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aMilitary courtsxGaza Strip. 0aMilitary courtsxWest Bank. 0aMilitary courtszGaza Strip. 0aMilitary courtszWest Bank. 0aPalestinian ArabsxCivil rightsxGaza StripxIsraelxWest Bank. 0aPalestinian ArabsxCivil rights. 0aRule of lawxIsrael. 0aRule of lawzIsrael. 0aWar and emergency powersxIsrael. 0aWar and emergency powerszIsrael. 7aHISTORY / Middle East / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package 2000-2015z978311066334108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520937987423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520937987.jpg  a978-3-11-066334-1  UC Press eBook Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-069042-2  UC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles